<mainContentHolder>

  <%# Rider FAQs %>
  <h3 class="text-3xl mb-4">Joining Sets</h3>
  <p class="font-bold">When can I join a set?</p>
  <p class="mb-3">Registration for sets of the week opens Sunday at 8pm CST. At this time until 11:59 pm Sunday night you may only join 1 set. If there are sets with available spots the following morning you are free to join them without restrictions.</p>
  
  <p class="font-bold">Why can’t I join a set even though I’m not already on it?</p>
  <p class="mb-3">If it’s Sunday, you will not be able to join any sets scheduled for the following week until 8pm CST. If it’s not Sunday, the Set may already be full or the set may have been scheduled for a past date. Your liability and waiver documents may also not have been signed or processed which will prohibit you from joining a set.</p>
  
  <p class="font-bold">Who can join a set?</p>
  <p class="mb-3">Anyone can join that is part of the organization.</p>
  
  <p class="font-bold">Do I need a signed waiver to sign up for sets?</p>
  <p class="mb-3">Yes all 3 waiver and liability documents must be signed and process in order to be able to sign up for sets.</p>
  
  <%# Driver FAQs %>
  <% if @user.has_role?("Driver") %>
    <h3 class="text-3xl">Creating Sets</h3>
    <h5 class="text-sm mb-4"><i>*Only available to Drivers</i></h5>
   
    <p class="font-bold">How can I create a set?</p>
    <p class="mb-3">You can create a set by clicking the “Rides” button in the top right navigation bar. Once the page loads, click on the “create set” button. From there, you can enter the date of the set and add up to 1 additional driver.</p>
  <% end %>

  <%# Treasury FAQs Drivers %>
  <% if @user.has_role?("Driver") %>
    <h3 class="text-3xl">Treasury FAQ's for Drivers</h3>
    <h5 class="text-sm mb-4"><i>*Only available to Drivers</i></h5>
   
    <p class="font-bold">How can I submit a receipt?</p>
    <p class="mb-3">You can submit a receipt by navigating to the "Receipts" page and clicking "Create a new Receipt". After this, fill out all of the spots in the form. For the image link, you must upload the photo on an external platform (ie Google Photos), and copy in the link here. </p>

    <p class="font-bold">How can I track a receipt?</p>
    <p class="mb-3">You can track a receipt by navigating to the "Receipts" viewing all receipts. These are broken down into stages depending upon where the receipt is in the approval process. You will know a refund request has been approved by the treasurer and send to SOFC if it is stage 2.</p>

    <p class="font-bold">How can I record I recieved a receipt refund?</p>
    <p class="mb-3">When you recieve a refund for a given receipt, simply open up the associated receipt on the "Receipts" page and click "I got my refund." After this, fill out the associated info and the refund will be fully tracked.</p>
  <% end %>

  <%# Treasury FAQs Treasurers %>
  <% if @user.has_role?("Treasurer") %>
    <h3 class="text-3xl">Treasury FAQ's for Treasurers</h3>
    <h5 class="text-sm mb-4"><i>*Only available to Treasurers</i></h5>
   
    <p class="font-bold">How can I submit a receipt?</p>
    <p class="mb-3">You can submit a receipt by navigating to the "Receipts" page and clicking "Create a new Receipt". After this, fill out all of the spots in the form. For the image link, you must upload the photo on an external platform (ie Google Photos), and copy in the link here. </p>

    <p class="font-bold">How can I track a receipt?</p>
    <p class="mb-3">You can track a receipt by navigating to the "Receipts" viewing all receipts. These are broken down into stages depending upon where the receipt is in the approval process. You will know a refund request has been approved by the treasurer and send to SOFC if it is stage 2.</p>

    <p class="font-bold">How can I accept or deny a receipt?</p>
    <p class="mb-3">When you see a receipt in stage 1, that means it is pending your approval. Open up the receipt and click "Edit this receipt" to move it to the next stage. Once opened, fill out the "Date approved" catory, and change the status column to Stage 2. Then as the treasurer you must use the info of this receipt to submit a refund request to SOFC. If you wish to deny a refund request, when opening a receipt simply click "Destroy this receipt."</p>
  <% end %>

